$ SQL*Plus: WHENEVER SQLERROR


{ WHENEVER SQLERROR EXIT

  `whenever sqlerror exit` has the same parameters as the ordinary `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/exit` command.

  Exit → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus as soon as an error is encountered (but print the error message):
gh|Oracle-patterns|/SQLPlus/whenever/sqlerror/exit.sql||

}
{ WHENEVER SQLERROR CONTINUE

  …

}


